SIMPLE: sensualism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensualism
<hw>Sen"su*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sensualisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition or
character of one who is sensual; subjection to sensual feelings and
appetite; sensuality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>The doctrine that all our
ideas, or the operations of the understanding, not only originate in
sensation, but are transformed sensations, copies or relics of
sensations; sensationalism; sensism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Ethics)</fld> <def>The regarding of the
gratification of the senses as the highest good.</def>
<rj><au>Krauth-Fleming.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensualist</ent>⟦br⟧
